The NMoves approach looks at the opponent's overall cooperation percentage 
and the last n moves (here, by default, n = 4). This strategy prints out 
the coefficients of our strategy. The first coefficient is the overall 
cooperation probability, the second is a constant, and 3rd to 6th represent 
the four moves. In general, a positive coefficient means that we are more likely 
to cooperate based on that variable while a negative means we are more likely 
to defect.
